Name: The Ritz-Carlton, Melbourne
Description:
Upmarket hotel featuring a chic restaurant, an indoor pool & a spa, plus harbour views.
In a modern tower with views of Victoria Harbour, this upmarket hotel is a 15-minute walk from the Melbourne Convention and Exhibition Centre, 3 km from the National Gallery of Victoria and 22 km from Melbourne Airport.
Polished rooms, some with harbour views, feature floor-to-ceiling windows and TVs, as well as minifridges and Wi-Fi. Suites have separate living rooms and dining areas. Club quarters allow access to a lounge with free cocktails. Room service is available 24/7.
There's a chic restaurant with skyline views, plus a cocktail bar, an indoor infinity pool, a spa and a 24/7 fitness centre. Parking and breakfast are available.

Name: Crown Towers Melbourne
Description:
High-end hotel with luxurious rooms & suites, plus an indoor pool, a gym & a sophisticated bar.
A kilometer from Flinders Street railway station, this high-end hotel overlooking the Yarra River is also 1 km from both the National Gallery of Victoria and Federation Square.
The upscale rooms and suites come with free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, iPod docks and city or bay views. Club level rooms add airy sitting areas and access to a lounge with complimentary breakfast and snacks. Suites have separate living areas and/or dining rooms. There's also a 1-bedroom villa with a study and a whirlpool tub.
Amenities include an indoor swimming pool, a fitness room and 2 rooftop tennis courts, plus a chic bar and a cocktail lounge.
Categories: Hotel, Bar, Business to business service, Conference center

Name: Grand Hyatt Melbourne
Description:
Posh high-rise property offering refined quarters with city views, plus an indoor pool & a spa.
Near shops and restaurants in the Central Business District, this posh high-rise hotel is a 7-minute walk from buzzy Federation Square, and a 14-minute walk from the National Gallery of Victoria.
Refined rooms offer floor-to-ceiling windows with city views, plus Wi-Fi (fee), flat-screens, iPod docks, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Club rooms provide access to a lounge with free Wi-Fi and breakfast. Suites add living and dining areas; some have kitchenettes and whirlpool tubs. Room service is available.
There's a fine-dining restaurant and a bistro, along with several bars. Other amenities include a heated indoor pool, a gym and a spa.

Name: Sofitel Melbourne on Collins
Description:
High-end hotel featuring bars & a modern brasserie, plus meeting spaces, ballrooms & a gym.
Among upscale shops on Collins Street, this premium hotel is 2 km from both the Melbourne Cricket Ground and the National Gallery of Victoria.
Classic rooms feature flat-screens, Wi-Fi (fee) and marble bathrooms and floor-to-ceiling windows. Club level rooms offer access to a lounge with perks such as breakfast and appetisers; studios and 1-bedroom suites add living areas. Room service is available. Kids age 11 and under (1 per room) stay at no charge with an adult.
Amenities include 2 trendy bars, a modern brasserie restaurant, and a lobby lounge with a fireplace. There's also a gym and a business centre, plus 12 meeting rooms and 3 ballrooms.

Name: Pullman Melbourne City Centre
Description:
Down-to-earth rooms & suites in a contemporary hotel offering a restaurant & a bar, plus a gym.
This modern hotel is 0.8 km from Federation Square, a 10-minute walk from Flinders Street Railway Station and 1.3 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
The relaxed rooms have Wi-Fi (fee) and flat-screen TVs, as well as minibars, microwaves, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Suites add separate living and dining areas. Room service is available 24/7.
There's an informal restaurant, an airy cafe and a cocktail bar, as well as a fitness room. Parking is available.

Name: voco Melbourne Central, an IHG Hotel
Description:
Sophisticated hotel offering an outdoor infinity pool & a gym, plus a steakhouse with a bar.
Amid shops and eateries, this polished hotel in a contemporary building is a 12-minute walk from Queen Victoria Market and 3 km from the Marvel Stadium. Melbourne Central train station is a 3-minute walk away.
Refined rooms offer Wi-Fi, TVs and safes, plus minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. All feature floor-to-ceiling windows with city views. Upgraded rooms add free-standing baths.
There's a plush steakhouse with a bar and a terrace. Other amenities include an exercise room and an outdoor infinity pool. Breakfast and limited parking are available.
Owner: voco Melbourne Central, an IHG Hotel (owner)

Name: Le M¨¦ridien Melbourne
Description:
Genteel hotel featuring chic rooms & suites, plus a French restaurant & an outdoor pool.
On a street lined with eateries and shops, this refined hotel with an art deco facade is a 7-minute walk from Parliament House, 9 minutes on foot from Chinatown and a minute's walk from a tram stop.
Chic rooms, some with Parliament House views, feature floor-to-ceiling windows, Wi-Fi and TVs, as well as minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking equipment. The 1- and 2-bedroom suites, some with dining tables, have separate living rooms.
There's a French restaurant and an art deco style cafe/bar, plus a 24/7 gym. Other amenities include an outdoor heated pool and a poolside bar with skyline views. Breakfast and parking are available.
Categories: Hotel, Meeting planning service, Wedding venue

Name: Mantra on Jolimont Melbourne
Description:
Informal apartment hotel featuring a restaurant/bar with a terrace, plus an outdoor pool & a gym.
A 6-minute walk from the William Barak Bridge/Melbourne Park tram stop, this informal apartment hotel is also a 7-minute walk from Melbourne Cricket Ground and 1 km from Federation Square.
The relaxed studios offer flat-screen TVs and Wi-Fi (fee), as well as kitchenettes. The 1- and 2-bedroom apartments have full kitchens and separate living rooms. Room service is available.
There's a casual restaurant with a terrace and a bar. Other amenities include a heated outdoor pool, a hot tub and a gym, plus a business centre and laundry facilities. Parking is available (surcharge).

Name: The Langham, Melbourne
Description:
Elegant lodging with river & city views, plus a spa, an indoor pool & a refined buffet restaurant.
Near shops and restaurants on the buzzy Southbank Promenade along the Yarra River, this luxe hotel is 13 minutes' walk from Crown Casino and a 2-minute walk from Flinders Street train station.
Refined rooms with handmade furniture feature smart TVs, minibars and free Wi-Fi. Upgraded rooms have river or city views, and some include patios or balconies. Club-level rooms add access to a lounge with complimentary breakfast, Suites provide whirlpool baths; upgraded suites offer kitchens. Room service is available 24/7.
There's a posh buffet restaurant with river views, and a chic lounge bar, plus a sleek spa, an indoor pool and a gym.

Name: Hilton Melbourne Little Queen Street
Description:
Bright quarters, some with city views, in an upmarket hotel offering a cocktail bar & a restaurant.
Set in a commercial area with eateries, this polished hotel is 1 km from the National Gallery of Victoria, a 13-minute walk from the bustling Queen Victoria Market and 7 minutes on foot from the Flagstaff train station.
Bright rooms come with Wi-Fi, smart TVs and sitting areas, along with blackout curtains and rainfall showers. Upgraded rooms have floor-to-ceiling windows and/or city views. Suites add living areas or separate living rooms. Connecting rooms are offered. Room service is available.
Amenities include an art deco style cocktail bar and a refined restaurant, along with a fitness centre. Breakfast and parking are available.

Name: Novotel Melbourne on Collins
Description:
Contemporary hotel offering an airy restaurant & a bar, plus an indoor pool & a gym.
This contemporary hotel is a 5-minute walk from Flinders Street rail station, 1.1 km from the historic Princess Theatre and 1.5 km from Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex.
The streamlined rooms and suites come with 40-inch flat-screen TVs, iPod docks and Wi-Fi (paid). They also include minibars and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Upgraded units add sofabeds. Room service is available.
There's an airy restaurant and a bar, as well as a gym and an indoor pool. Other amenities include an airport shuttle, laundry facilities and valet parking. Babysitting services are available for a fee.

Name: YTI Garden Hotel
Description:
Unassuming hotel in the city centre offering warm rooms & apartments, plus complimentary Wi-Fi.
In the Central Business District, this down-to-earth hotel is a 1-minute walk from the nearest tram stop and a 14-minute walk from the Queen Victoria Market.
Warmly decorated rooms feature free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs and fridges, plus tea and coffeemaking facilities. Simple apartments, ranging from studios to 2-bedroom units, add kitchenettes. Children age 12 and under stay with adults at no extra cost.
Coin-operated laundry facilities are available.

Name: Mercure Welcome Melbourne
Description:
Relaxed rooms in a modern lodging featuring a cafe, a grill restaurant & a cocktail bar.
A 5-minute walk from Melbourne Central rail station, this modern, city-centre hotel with a polished facade is 2.1 km from the Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex, and 3.4 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
The casual rooms offer Wi-Fi (fee), minifridges and flat-screen TVs, plus tea and coffeemaking facilities. Upgraded quarters add kitchenettes and sitting areas. Room service and rollaway beds are available.
Amenities include a bright grill restaurant, a cosy cocktail bar and a cafe, plus a business centre, event/meeting space and a kids' club. A breakfast buffet and covered parking are offered for a surcharge.

Name: W Melbourne
Description:
Fashionable rooms & suites in a posh hotel offering swanky eateries, bars & an indoor pool.
In a striking high-rise in the Central Business District, this ultrahip hotel is an 8-minute walk from Flinders Street railway station and 1 km from Queen Victoria Market.
Featuring floor-to-ceiling windows, the fashionable rooms provide Wi-Fi and flat-screens, plus minibars, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Upgraded rooms add city views, and suites offer sitting areas or separate living rooms. Upgraded suites include dining tables, bar areas and/or balconies. Room service is available 24/7.
Amenities consist of 3 chic eateries and 2 stylish bars, as well as a gym, and an indoor pool that has city views. Parking is available.
Categories: Hotel, Meeting planning service, Wedding venue

Name: Ovolo South Yarra
Description:
Retro-style quarters in a hip hotel offering a restaurant & a bar, plus a 24-hour fitness centre.
A 3-minute walk from South Yarra train station, this hip hotel with a glass-and-steel facade is 2 km from the Royal Botanic Gardens Victoria - Melbourne Gardens and 5 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
Cosy, retro-style rooms feature Wi-Fi and smart TVs, plus minibars, tea and coffeemaking facilities, and safes. Upgraded rooms have sitting areas with pull-out sofas, and rock star¨Cinspired suites add wet bars.
There¡¯s a funky restaurant and bar, as well as guest laundry facilities and a 24-hour fitness centre. Breakfast is available.

Name: Europa Melbourne
Description:
Utilitarian dorms & rooms with shared bathrooms in a functional lodging featuring a rooftop terrace.
A 4-minute walk from train service at Melbourne Central Station, this pared-down hostel is an 8-minute walk from Queen Victoria Market and 3 km from the Royal Botanic Gardens.
Straightforward mixed-sex and female-only dorms sleep up to 12 guests, and come with bunk beds, lockers and linens. Private rooms add flat-screen TVs. Bathrooms are shared.
There's a rooftop terrace.

Name: Melbourne City Backpackers
Description:
Relaxed hostel offering simple dorms & private rooms, plus a kitchen, a lounge & breakfast.
A 6-minute walk from Southern Cross train station, this laid-back hostel is 1 km from Queen Victoria Market and 2 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
The utilitarian mixed-gender or female-only dorms offer Wi-Fi, bunk beds, reading lights and lockers, plus shared bathrooms. Private rooms are also available. Bed linen is provided.
Breakfast is available. Other amenities include a communal kitchen and a lounge, as well as computers for guest use. There's also a coin-operated laundry.

Name: South Yarra Hostel
Description:
Casual adults-only hostel in a 19th-century property offering unfussy rooms & dorms, plus a kitchen.
In a 19th-century Victorian building, this relaxed adults-only hostel is a 5-minute walk from Windsor tram station, 3 km from roller coasters and rides at Luna Park and 4 km from St Kilda Beach.
Unfussy dorms and private rooms include free linen, Wi-Fi and lockers, plus shared bathrooms. Dorms feature bunk beds.
Amenities include a communal kitchen, a barbecue area, and a lounge with cable TV. Breakfast and coin-operated laundry facilities are available.
Categories: Hostel, Self-catering accommodation, Student housing center

Name: Abbotsford Private Rooms & Pods @ 15 Charles Homestay
Description:
Casual rooms, some with shared bathrooms, in an unassuming hostel offering breakfast & Wi-Fi.
Set in a residential area a 3-minute walk from North Richmond Station, this unpretentious hostel is 2 km from Fitzroy Gardens and 5 km from Queen Victoria Market.
Basic capsule rooms provide Wi-Fi and lockers. Some have no windows. Bathrooms are shared. Upgraded airy rooms add minibars and/or en suite bathrooms.
Continental breakfast is offered. Other amenities include a shared kitchen, a dining area and a lounge with a flat-screen TV, as well as a garden with outdoor seating. Guest laundry facilities are available.
Owner: Abbotsford Private Rooms & Pods @ 15 Charles Homestay (owner)

Name: Bayside House
Description:
Relaxed property with modest dorms & private rooms, plus complimentary Wi-Fi & breakfast.
In a commercial area off Route 3, this laid-back hostel is a 2-minute walk from the St Kilda Junction tram stop and 3 km from St Kilda Beach.
Modest mixed-gender and female-only dorms, some with exposed brick walls, have bunk beds and sleep up to 12 people. Wi-Fi is free. Bathrooms are shared. Private rooms with en suite facilities are available.
Breakfast is complimentary. There's also a communal kitchen. Vibrant common lounge areas feature artwork and table tennis.
Categories: Hostel, Hotel, Motel, Self-catering accommodation, Student housing center, Youth hostel

Name: Nomads St Kilda
Description:
Basic dorms & private rooms in a casual hostel offering a shared kitchen, a TV lounge & a bar.
A 4-minute walk from amusement rides at Luna Park, this casual hostel with a colourful exterior is a 6-minute walk from 1920s Palais Theatre and a 9-minute walk from St. Kilda Beach.
Straightforward mixed-gender or female-only dorms offer lockers and bunk beds, plus en suite bathrooms. Private rooms add flat-screens. Wi-Fi is available for a fee.
Amenities include a shared kitchen, a TV lounge and a pool table. There's also a lively bar and guest laundry facilities.

Name: City Centre Budget Hotel
Description:
Low-key rooms & suites in a casual hotel featuring a shared kitchen, a rooftop terrace & free Wi-Fi.
Adjacent to Parliament train station, this modern budget hotel is an 8-minute walk from the Swanston Street shopping precinct and 11 minutes on foot from Federation Square.
Laid-back rooms offer free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs, as well as fans, minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking facilities; bathrooms are shared. Studios add en suite bathrooms and kitchens; some have bunk beds. A sophisticated 1-bedroom apartment features a separate living room, a balcony and a washer/dryer. There's no air-conditioning.
Amenities include a communal kitchen, guest laundry facilities and a rooftop terrace. Parking is available for a fee.

Name: Ritz Backpackers
Description:
Simple private & shared quarters in a hip adults-only hostel with free breakfast & Wi-Fi.
Set above a bar on a bustling street corner 4 minutes by foot from a tram stop, this hip adults-only hostel is 2 km from both St. Kilda Beach and Luna Park.
Simple accommodations range from private rooms with minifridges to mixed-gender dorms with up to 10 bunk beds. All come with free Wi-Fi, linens and towels, and en suite bathrooms. Dorms offer private lockers.
Free perks include daily pancake breakfast, and BBQ dinner, or regular socials with wine and cheese. There¡¯s a shared kitchenette, a terrace and an area with a TV and a pool table. Guest laundry facilities are available.

Name: YTI Garden Hotel
Description:
Unassuming hotel in the city centre offering warm rooms & apartments, plus complimentary Wi-Fi.
In the Central Business District, this down-to-earth hotel is a 1-minute walk from the nearest tram stop and a 14-minute walk from the Queen Victoria Market.
Warmly decorated rooms feature free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs and fridges, plus tea and coffeemaking facilities. Simple apartments, ranging from studios to 2-bedroom units, add kitchenettes. Children age 12 and under stay with adults at no extra cost.
Coin-operated laundry facilities are available.

Name: ibis budget Melbourne CBD
Description:
Unassuming hotel in a Victorian building, featuring compact, down-to-earth rooms with minifridges.
Set in a Victorian building on a road lined with shops, this modest budget hotel in the Central Business District is a 6-minute walk from Flinders Street train station, 2 km from the Royal Exhibition Building and a 10-minute walk from the Melbourne Skydeck.
The compact, warmly furnished rooms feature Wi-Fi (surcharge) and flat-screen TVs, as well as minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking equipment. Upgraded rooms add sofas.
A continental breakfast buffet is offered for a fee. There's also a coin-operated laundry.

Name: Mercure Welcome Melbourne
Description:
Relaxed rooms in a modern lodging featuring a cafe, a grill restaurant & a cocktail bar.
A 5-minute walk from Melbourne Central rail station, this modern, city-centre hotel with a polished facade is 2.1 km from the Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex, and 3.4 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
The casual rooms offer Wi-Fi (fee), minifridges and flat-screen TVs, plus tea and coffeemaking facilities. Upgraded quarters add kitchenettes and sitting areas. Room service and rollaway beds are available.
Amenities include a bright grill restaurant, a cosy cocktail bar and a cafe, plus a business centre, event/meeting space and a kids' club. A breakfast buffet and covered parking are offered for a surcharge.

Name: City Square Motel
Description:
Streamlined hotel offering unfussy rooms with minifridges, microwaves & free Wi-Fi.
On a bustling tree-lined street with shops, this low-key motel is 3 minutes' walk from the train and tram stations, and 2 km from both the historic Queen Victoria Market, and the Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex.
The simple rooms have free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, minifridges and microwaves, as well as tea and coffeemaking facilities. Some rooms add sofabeds on request. Children aged 12 and under stay at no cost in parents' rooms.
Parking is available for a fee.

Name: The Victoria Hotel
Description:
Modest hotel offering unfussy rooms, plus a pool, a sauna & a restaurant serving modern cuisine.
Near shops, restaurants and entertainment in the city centre, this relaxed hotel is a 6-minute walk from Flinders Street train station, a kilometre from the National Gallery of Victoria, and 2 km from the Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex.
The unassuming rooms feature free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, desks, and tea and coffeemaking facilities.
There's an onsite restaurant serving modern cuisine and a breakfast buffet, plus an indoor pool. Other amenities include a hot tub, a sauna and a fitness room. Indoor parking is offered for a fee.

Name: HOTEL NO
Description:
Offbeat hotel on a car park rooftop, offering minimalist suites in funky 1970s trailers.
Occupying 1970s chrome trailers located on a car park rooftop in the Central Business District, this quirky hotel is 12 minutes' walk from both Southern Cross railway station and Federation Square, a bustling plaza with abstract buildings.
Set around a communal courtyard, the 5 cosy, minimalist suites provide complimentary minibars, as well as air-conditioning, en suite bathrooms, iPads and furnished terraces. An upgraded suite adds an outdoor hot tub. Wi-Fi access is available.

Name: YEHS Melbourne Hotel CBD
Description:
Simple, colourful quarters, some with kitchens, in an unassuming hotel offering a cafe.
Set in the Central Business District, this casual hotel is 2 km from Queen Victoria Market and 4 km from the National Gallery of Victoria. Southern Cross train station is a 5-minute walk away.
Streamlined rooms with colourful accent walls offer Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs and minifridges. Upgraded rooms add sitting areas. The 1-bedroom apartments feature kitchens and living rooms.
There's an informal cafe. Breakfast is available.

Name: ibis Styles Kingsgate
Description:
Laid-back rooms in a relaxed hotel featuring free Wi-Fi, a French restaurant & a cafe.
Set in a circa-1926 building in Melbourne's city centre, this casual hotel is a 4-minute walk from Southern Cross train station, a 10-minute walk from Etihad Stadium, and a 13-minute walk from the Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex.
The relaxed rooms offer bright furnishings, desks, and tea and coffeemaking facilities, plus free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs. Kids age 15 and under stay free with a parent.
There's a cafe/bar and an airy French restaurant. A breakfast buffet is available for a fee.

Name: City Park Hotel
Description:
Warm rooms & suites in a relaxed property offering a bar/restaurant, plus free Wi-Fi & parking.
This unfussy hotel is 2 km from the Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex, 3 km from the Royal Botanic Gardens Victoria and 29 km from the Melbourne Airport.
Warm, unassuming rooms feature free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs. Suites come with whirlpool tubs. Adjoining rooms and room service are offered.
Parking is included. There's an informal restaurant/bar. Breakfast and an airport shuttle can be arranged for a surcharge.

Name: Comfort Hotel East Melbourne
Description:
Contemporary rooms with wet bars in a laid-back hotel featuring complimentary Wi-Fi & parking.
A 5-minute walk from the nearest light-rail stop, this low-key hotel is 2 km from Melbourne's city centre and 3 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
The modern, down-to-earth rooms feature sitting areas, free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs, as well as wet bars with minifridges, microwaves, and tea and coffeemaking facilities.
Parking is complimentary.

Name: Best Western Melbourne City Hotel
Description:
Laid-back hotel featuring a cafe/bar & a rooftop terrace, plus complimentary Wi-Fi.
A 4-minute walk from Southern Cross train station, this casual hotel in the Central Business District is a 5-minute walk from Sea Life Melbourne Aquarium and 2 km from Queen Victoria Market.
Straightforward room offer free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs and minifridges, plus tea and coffeemaking facilities. Upgraded rooms add private terraces. Apartments feature kitchenettes. Room service is available.
Amenities include a relaxed cafe/bar and a rooftop terrace with sitting areas. Parking and breakfast are available for a fee. Pets are welcome.

Name: Georgian Court Bed and Breakfast
Description:
Basic rooms in a 1900s townhouse-turned-traditional B&B with a guest lounge & free parking.
Set in a 1900s townhouse on a tree-lined street, this traditional bed-and-breakfast is a 4-minute walk from Punt Road/Bridge Road tram stop, and 2 km from the museums and restaurants at Federation Square.
Basic rooms come with Wi-Fi access, TVs and minifridges, as well as tea and coffeemaking equipment. Most rooms have en suite bathrooms, and others provide shared or private facilities. Upgraded rooms add whirlpool baths.
A breakfast buffet is served in a cosy dining room. Limited parking is complimentary. Other amenities include a lounge and guest laundry facilities.

Name: Europa Melbourne
Description:
Utilitarian dorms & rooms with shared bathrooms in a functional lodging featuring a rooftop terrace.
A 4-minute walk from train service at Melbourne Central Station, this pared-down hostel is an 8-minute walk from Queen Victoria Market and 3 km from the Royal Botanic Gardens.
Straightforward mixed-sex and female-only dorms sleep up to 12 guests, and come with bunk beds, lockers and linens. Private rooms add flat-screen TVs. Bathrooms are shared.
There's a rooftop terrace.

Name: City Limits Hotel
Description:
Unpretentious hotel offering bright rooms with complimentary Wi-Fi and wet bars.
Set in Chinatown, this straightforward hotel is a 3-minute walk from the Spring St/Bourke St tram stop and 2 km from Sea Life Melbourne Aquarium.
The bright rooms provide free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, seating areas and desks, as well as wet bars with minifridges and microwaves.
There's a business centre and a 24-hour reception. Parking and breakfast are available for an additional fee.

Name: City Edge Serviced Apartments
Description:
Straightforward apartment hotel offering casual quarters with kitchens, plus a guest laundry.
A 10-minute walk from North Richmond train station, this straightforward apartment hotel is also 14 minutes' walk from Melbourne Cricket Ground and 2 km from the Rod Laver Arena.
Informal studios feature kitchens and sitting areas, as well as free Wi-Fi and flat-screen TVs. The 1- and 2-bedroom apartments add separate living rooms.
Parking is complimentary. There's a coin-operated laundry, and continental breakfast is available for a fee.

Name: Melbourne City Backpackers
Description:
Relaxed hostel offering simple dorms & private rooms, plus a kitchen, a lounge & breakfast.
A 6-minute walk from Southern Cross train station, this laid-back hostel is 1 km from Queen Victoria Market and 2 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
The utilitarian mixed-gender or female-only dorms offer Wi-Fi, bunk beds, reading lights and lockers, plus shared bathrooms. Private rooms are also available. Bed linen is provided.
Breakfast is available. Other amenities include a communal kitchen and a lounge, as well as computers for guest use. There's also a coin-operated laundry.

Name: South Yarra Hostel
Description:
Casual adults-only hostel in a 19th-century property offering unfussy rooms & dorms, plus a kitchen.
In a 19th-century Victorian building, this relaxed adults-only hostel is a 5-minute walk from Windsor tram station, 3 km from roller coasters and rides at Luna Park and 4 km from St Kilda Beach.
Unfussy dorms and private rooms include free linen, Wi-Fi and lockers, plus shared bathrooms. Dorms feature bunk beds.
Amenities include a communal kitchen, a barbecue area, and a lounge with cable TV. Breakfast and coin-operated laundry facilities are available.
Categories: Hostel, Self-catering accommodation, Student housing center

Name: Birches Serviced Apartments
Description:
Contemporary apartments and a townhouse offering free Wi-Fi, plus a courtyard with a BBQ grill.
Set in the fashionable East Melbourne district, these contemporary apartments are 2 km from Richmond's vibrant restaurant and retail scene, and 3.6 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
Featuring fully equipped kitchens, the modern 1-bedroom apartments offer free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs with satellite channels, DVD players and sofabeds. There's also a 2-bedroom Victorian townhouse with a furnished courtyard and a BBQ.
There's a communal courtyard with a barbecue. Parking is available for a surcharge.

Description:

Description:
Understated rooms & suites in a hip hotel offering a restaurant, a fitness centre & an indoor pool.

The contemporary rooms and suites include sitting areas, flat-screen TVs and free limited Wi-Fi, along with desks, minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Some quarters offer city or harbour views.
A complimentary continental breakfast buffet is provided. There's an indoor pool, a sauna and a gym, plus a business centre and parking (surcharge).

Name: The Ritz-Carlton, Melbourne
Description:
Upmarket hotel featuring a chic restaurant, an indoor pool & a spa, plus harbour views.
In a modern tower with views of Victoria Harbour, this upmarket hotel is a 15-minute walk from the Melbourne Convention and Exhibition Centre, 3 km from the National Gallery of Victoria and 22 km from Melbourne Airport.
Polished rooms, some with harbour views, feature floor-to-ceiling windows and TVs, as well as minifridges and Wi-Fi. Suites have separate living rooms and dining areas. Club quarters allow access to a lounge with free cocktails. Room service is available 24/7.
There's a chic restaurant with skyline views, plus a cocktail bar, an indoor infinity pool, a spa and a 24/7 fitness centre. Parking and breakfast are available.

Name: Crown Towers Melbourne
Description:
High-end hotel with luxurious rooms & suites, plus an indoor pool, a gym & a sophisticated bar.
A kilometer from Flinders Street railway station, this high-end hotel overlooking the Yarra River is also 1 km from both the National Gallery of Victoria and Federation Square.
The upscale rooms and suites come with free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, iPod docks and city or bay views. Club level rooms add airy sitting areas and access to a lounge with complimentary breakfast and snacks. Suites have separate living areas and/or dining rooms. There's also a 1-bedroom villa with a study and a whirlpool tub.
Amenities include an indoor swimming pool, a fitness room and 2 rooftop tennis courts, plus a chic bar and a cocktail lounge.
Categories: Hotel, Bar, Business to business service, Conference center

Name: Grand Hyatt Melbourne
Description:
Posh high-rise property offering refined quarters with city views, plus an indoor pool & a spa.
Near shops and restaurants in the Central Business District, this posh high-rise hotel is a 7-minute walk from buzzy Federation Square, and a 14-minute walk from the National Gallery of Victoria.
Refined rooms offer floor-to-ceiling windows with city views, plus Wi-Fi (fee), flat-screens, iPod docks, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Club rooms provide access to a lounge with free Wi-Fi and breakfast. Suites add living and dining areas; some have kitchenettes and whirlpool tubs. Room service is available.
There's a fine-dining restaurant and a bistro, along with several bars. Other amenities include a heated indoor pool, a gym and a spa.

Name: voco Melbourne Central, an IHG Hotel
Description:
Sophisticated hotel offering an outdoor infinity pool & a gym, plus a steakhouse with a bar.
Amid shops and eateries, this polished hotel in a contemporary building is a 12-minute walk from Queen Victoria Market and 3 km from the Marvel Stadium. Melbourne Central train station is a 3-minute walk away.
Refined rooms offer Wi-Fi, TVs and safes, plus minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. All feature floor-to-ceiling windows with city views. Upgraded rooms add free-standing baths.
There's a plush steakhouse with a bar and a terrace. Other amenities include an exercise room and an outdoor infinity pool. Breakfast and limited parking are available.
Owner: voco Melbourne Central, an IHG Hotel (owner)

Name: Sofitel Melbourne on Collins
Description:
High-end hotel featuring bars & a modern brasserie, plus meeting spaces, ballrooms & a gym.
Among upscale shops on Collins Street, this premium hotel is 2 km from both the Melbourne Cricket Ground and the National Gallery of Victoria.
Classic rooms feature flat-screens, Wi-Fi (fee) and marble bathrooms and floor-to-ceiling windows. Club level rooms offer access to a lounge with perks such as breakfast and appetisers; studios and 1-bedroom suites add living areas. Room service is available. Kids age 11 and under (1 per room) stay at no charge with an adult.
Amenities include 2 trendy bars, a modern brasserie restaurant, and a lobby lounge with a fireplace. There's also a gym and a business centre, plus 12 meeting rooms and 3 ballrooms.

Name: Melbourne Marriott Hotel Docklands
Description:
Chic rooms in an upmarket riverfront hotel with a rooftop infinity pool, plus a restaurant & bars.
In the Docklands shopping and dining district along the Yarra River, this upscale hotel is a 2-minute walk from a tram stop. It's 3 km from the Queen Victoria Market and 6 km from the Melbourne Skydeck.
Chic rooms have Wi-Fi, minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Some offer river views. Club rooms add access to a private lounge with afternoon and evening snacks. Room service is available 24/7.
A rooftop terrace features an infinity pool, a kids' pool, a hot tub, and a bar serving small plates. Other amenities include a modern restaurant, a sleek cocktail bar and a coffee shop, as well as a gym. Breakfast and parking are available.

Name: The Langham, Melbourne
Description:
Elegant lodging with river & city views, plus a spa, an indoor pool & a refined buffet restaurant.
Near shops and restaurants on the buzzy Southbank Promenade along the Yarra River, this luxe hotel is 13 minutes' walk from Crown Casino and a 2-minute walk from Flinders Street train station.
Refined rooms with handmade furniture feature smart TVs, minibars and free Wi-Fi. Upgraded rooms have river or city views, and some include patios or balconies. Club-level rooms add access to a lounge with complimentary breakfast, Suites provide whirlpool baths; upgraded suites offer kitchens. Room service is available 24/7.
There's a posh buffet restaurant with river views, and a chic lounge bar, plus a sleek spa, an indoor pool and a gym.

Name: Mantra on Jolimont Melbourne
Description:
Informal apartment hotel featuring a restaurant/bar with a terrace, plus an outdoor pool & a gym.
A 6-minute walk from the William Barak Bridge/Melbourne Park tram stop, this informal apartment hotel is also a 7-minute walk from Melbourne Cricket Ground and 1 km from Federation Square.
The relaxed studios offer flat-screen TVs and Wi-Fi (fee), as well as kitchenettes. The 1- and 2-bedroom apartments have full kitchens and separate living rooms. Room service is available.
There's a casual restaurant with a terrace and a bar. Other amenities include a heated outdoor pool, a hot tub and a gym, plus a business centre and laundry facilities. Parking is available (surcharge).

Name: Hilton Melbourne Little Queen Street
Description:
Bright quarters, some with city views, in an upmarket hotel offering a cocktail bar & a restaurant.
Set in a commercial area with eateries, this polished hotel is 1 km from the National Gallery of Victoria, a 13-minute walk from the bustling Queen Victoria Market and 7 minutes on foot from the Flagstaff train station.
Bright rooms come with Wi-Fi, smart TVs and sitting areas, along with blackout curtains and rainfall showers. Upgraded rooms have floor-to-ceiling windows and/or city views. Suites add living areas or separate living rooms. Connecting rooms are offered. Room service is available.
Amenities include an art deco style cocktail bar and a refined restaurant, along with a fitness centre. Breakfast and parking are available.

Name: Pullman Melbourne City Centre
Description:
Down-to-earth rooms & suites in a contemporary hotel offering a restaurant & a bar, plus a gym.
This modern hotel is 0.8 km from Federation Square, a 10-minute walk from Flinders Street Railway Station and 1.3 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
The relaxed rooms have Wi-Fi (fee) and flat-screen TVs, as well as minibars, microwaves, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Suites add separate living and dining areas. Room service is available 24/7.
There's an informal restaurant, an airy cafe and a cocktail bar, as well as a fitness room. Parking is available.

Name: Hyatt Centric Melbourne
Description:
Minimalist rooms in an upmarket hotel offering an indoor pool, a modern restaurant & bay views.
Featuring views of the Yarra River and Port Philip Bay, this upscale hotel is a 14-minute walk from Melbourne Skydeck, 1 km from the Federation Square cultural hub and 5 minutes on foot from Southern Cross railway station.
Minimalist rooms provide smart TVs, Chromecast and Wi-Fi, as well as Nespresso machines, kettles and minifridges. Upgraded rooms add balconies and/or bay views.
There's a modern restaurant, a cafe, and a bar with river views. Breakfast is available. Other amenities include an indoor pool, a gym and a terrace, plus parking.

Name: Novotel Melbourne on Collins
Description:
Contemporary hotel offering an airy restaurant & a bar, plus an indoor pool & a gym.
This contemporary hotel is a 5-minute walk from Flinders Street rail station, 1.1 km from the historic Princess Theatre and 1.5 km from Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex.
The streamlined rooms and suites come with 40-inch flat-screen TVs, iPod docks and Wi-Fi (paid). They also include minibars and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Upgraded units add sofabeds. Room service is available.
There's an airy restaurant and a bar, as well as a gym and an indoor pool. Other amenities include an airport shuttle, laundry facilities and valet parking. Babysitting services are available for a fee.

Name: Le M¨¦ridien Melbourne
Description:
Genteel hotel featuring chic rooms & suites, plus a French restaurant & an outdoor pool.
On a street lined with eateries and shops, this refined hotel with an art deco facade is a 7-minute walk from Parliament House, 9 minutes on foot from Chinatown and a minute's walk from a tram stop.
Chic rooms, some with Parliament House views, feature floor-to-ceiling windows, Wi-Fi and TVs, as well as minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking equipment. The 1- and 2-bedroom suites, some with dining tables, have separate living rooms.
There's a French restaurant and an art deco style cafe/bar, plus a 24/7 gym. Other amenities include an outdoor heated pool and a poolside bar with skyline views. Breakfast and parking are available.
Categories: Hotel, Meeting planning service, Wedding venue

Name: YTI Garden Hotel
Description:
Unassuming hotel in the city centre offering warm rooms & apartments, plus complimentary Wi-Fi.
In the Central Business District, this down-to-earth hotel is a 1-minute walk from the nearest tram stop and a 14-minute walk from the Queen Victoria Market.
Warmly decorated rooms feature free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs and fridges, plus tea and coffeemaking facilities. Simple apartments, ranging from studios to 2-bedroom units, add kitchenettes. Children age 12 and under stay with adults at no extra cost.
Coin-operated laundry facilities are available.

Name: W Melbourne
Description:
Fashionable rooms & suites in a posh hotel offering swanky eateries, bars & an indoor pool.
In a striking high-rise in the Central Business District, this ultrahip hotel is an 8-minute walk from Flinders Street railway station and 1 km from Queen Victoria Market.
Featuring floor-to-ceiling windows, the fashionable rooms provide Wi-Fi and flat-screens, plus minibars, and tea and coffeemaking facilities. Upgraded rooms add city views, and suites offer sitting areas or separate living rooms. Upgraded suites include dining tables, bar areas and/or balconies. Room service is available 24/7.
Amenities consist of 3 chic eateries and 2 stylish bars, as well as a gym, and an indoor pool that has city views. Parking is available.
Categories: Hotel, Meeting planning service, Wedding venue

Name: ibis budget Melbourne CBD
Description:
Unassuming hotel in a Victorian building, featuring compact, down-to-earth rooms with minifridges.
Set in a Victorian building on a road lined with shops, this modest budget hotel in the Central Business District is a 6-minute walk from Flinders Street train station, 2 km from the Royal Exhibition Building and a 10-minute walk from the Melbourne Skydeck.
The compact, warmly furnished rooms feature Wi-Fi (surcharge) and flat-screen TVs, as well as minifridges, and tea and coffeemaking equipment. Upgraded rooms add sofas.
A continental breakfast buffet is offered for a fee. There's also a coin-operated laundry.

Name: Adina Apartment Hotel Melbourne
Description:
Contemporary apartments in a polished hotel with a restaurant/bar & a gym with a pool.
This modern apartment hotel in central Melbourne is 1.3 km from the architecturally notable Federation Square, and 1.6 km from both the National Gallery of Victoria, and the Crown Casino and Entertainment Complex.
Featuring open-plan kitchen, lounge and dining areas, the bright, contemporary apartments have washer/dryers, flat-screen TVs and Wi-Fi (fees may apply). Upgraded units add balconies, loft bedrooms or floor-to-ceiling windows. Room service is available.
Amenities include a casual restaurant/bar, as well as a gym with an indoor lap pool and a sauna. There are also 5 conference rooms.
Categories: Hotel, Event venue, Extended stay hotel, Holiday apartment rental, Serviced accommodation

Name: Ovolo South Yarra
Description:
Retro-style quarters in a hip hotel offering a restaurant & a bar, plus a 24-hour fitness centre.
A 3-minute walk from South Yarra train station, this hip hotel with a glass-and-steel facade is 2 km from the Royal Botanic Gardens Victoria - Melbourne Gardens and 5 km from the National Gallery of Victoria.
Cosy, retro-style rooms feature Wi-Fi and smart TVs, plus minibars, tea and coffeemaking facilities, and safes. Upgraded rooms have sitting areas with pull-out sofas, and rock star¨Cinspired suites add wet bars.
There¡¯s a funky restaurant and bar, as well as guest laundry facilities and a 24-hour fitness centre. Breakfast is available.
